 although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Nicholas DeGraham was born in 1272. He had at least 1 son with Maria de Strathearn. He died in 1304, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1272–1304":"1272–1304","1248–1318":"1248–1318","1278–1337":"1278–1337","1304":"1304","1337":"1337","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1272":"1272","about 1278":"umbes 1278","1318":"1318","Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1272–1304":"1272–1304","1248–1318":"1248–1318","1278–1337":"1278–1337","1304":"1304","1337":"1337","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1272":"1272","about 1278":"noin 1278","1318":"1318","Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1272–1304":"1272–1304","1248–1318":"1248–1318","1278–1337":"1278–1337","1304":"1304","1337":"1337","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1272":"1272","about 1278":"environ 1278","1318":"1318","Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Scotland":"Abercorn, Linlithgowshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Nicholas DeGraham est né en 1272. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Maria de Strathearn. Il est décédé en 1304, à l’âge de 32 ans."},"de":{"1272–1304":"1272–1304","1248–1318":"1248–1318","1278–1337":"1278–1337","1304":"1304","1337":"1337","1248":"1248","1278":"1278","1272":"1272","about 1278"